<dsc type="combined">
<c01 level="series"><did><unittitle>Correspondence</unittitle></did><scopecontent><p>The Correspondence dates from 1893 to 1949 and includes correspondence from such notables as C. W. Baldwin, Charles M. Barton, Charles W. Brashares, William R. Cook, Henry H. Crane, Harry E. Fosdick, Edward S. Johnson, Frederick D. Leete, Ben B. Lindsey, G. Bromley Oxnam, and Marshall R. Reed.</p></scopecontent>
<c02 level="file"><did><container type="box" label="Box">1</container><unittitle><unitdate type="inclusive" normal="1893/1949">1893-1949</unitdate>   <unitdate>undated</unitdate></unittitle><physdesc><extent>25 folders</extent></physdesc></did></c02></c01>
<c01 level="series"><did><unittitle>Ministerial Papers</unittitle></did><scopecontent><p>Ministerial Papers includes a 1944 report of the Peoples' Congress of Applied Religion and miscellaneous other papers of the Detroit Conference of the Methodist Episcopal Church.</p></scopecontent>
<c02 level="file"><did><container type="box" label="Box">1</container><unittitle>Report of the Peoples' Congress of Applied Religion, <unitdate type="inclusive" normal="1944">1944</unitdate></unittitle></did></c02>
<c02 level="file"><did><container type="box" label="Box">1</container><unittitle>Detroit Conference of the Methodist Episcopal Church miscellanea</unittitle><physdesc><extent>12 folders</extent></physdesc></did></c02></c01>
<c01 level="series"><did><unittitle>Miscellaneous</unittitle></did><scopecontent><p>Miscellaneous consists of personal items, financial materials relating to his work on behalf of retired ministers; scattered records of Superior Township, Washtenaw County and Plymouth Township, Wayne County, Michigan; and photographs.</p></scopecontent>
<c02 level="file"><did><container type="box" label="Box">1</container><unittitle>Personal miscellanea</unittitle></did></c02>
